ORLANDO Pirates have confirmed more departures ahead of the upcoming 2022-23 season. The club confirmed on their website that they have loaned out Nkanyiso Zungu to Richards Bay FC, while strikers Tshegofatso Mabasa and Boitumelo Radiopane will be joining Sekhukhune United and Cape Town Spurs respectively. Bongani Sam will move to KwaZulu Natal province where he will join Maritzburg United also on a season long loan deal. ?? ?? ???????????????? ???????????? ???? Read the Loan News ???? https://t.co/4DKJUEKvqG????????#OrlandoPirates#OnceAlways pic.twitter.com/XiUOdXY09Y  